  "texts": [
    "Causal representation learning aims at building DNNs that are only using causal links in the data and thus capture the complex cause-and-effect relationships in the system 106.",
    "While this area is still under active research, developing ML models and especially FMs for EWS should aim to observe causality.",
    "For instance, a causal model can evaluate the impact of interventions and thus understand the differences between the observed world and what might have occurred without humanitarian action.",
    "Additionally, causal modelsare interpretable by construction;, for example, a causal model for wildfires could disentangle complex driving relations beyond spurious correlations, and could reveal an increased wildfire danger if, in addition to high heat, there is also prolonged water stress and specific socioeconomic conditions.",
    "Moving towards FMs for EWS, an inherent property of generative models becomes a challenge: the generation of seemingly credible yet incorrect information termed hallucination 107."
  ],
